item.ambientadditions.pembroke_corgi_spa: 彭布罗克柯基犬刷怪蛋
tooltip.ambientadditions.yeti_feeders: Slowly restores hunger when the wearer is in water or rain.
tooltip.ambientadditions.ducky_mask: Makes the wearer less intimidating towards certain skittish animals.
tooltip.ambientadditions.fun_fact.aye_ay: These nocturnal primates have been proclaimed to be a bad omen!
tooltip.ambientadditions.fun_fact.blue_s: The blue spots on these rays warn of their venomous barb!
tooltip.ambientadditions.fun_fact.blunth: These arboreal snakes have huge eyes, making up 26% of their head!
tooltip.ambientadditions.fun_fact.cardig: It's called 'splooting' when a corgi lies down on its stomach with its back legs stretched out!
tooltip.ambientadditions.fun_fact.chocol: These sea creatures were named after the spiny growths on their body, which resemble chocolate chips!
tooltip.ambientadditions.fun_fact.giant_: Needing a steady supply of calcium to grow, these snails will dine on many things, including concrete!
tooltip.ambientadditions.fun_fact.harleq: These crustaceans dine on the limbs of a starfish!
tooltip.ambientadditions.fun_fact.hoatzi: One of the few birds to possess claws that nestlings use for climbing!
tooltip.ambientadditions.fun_fact.iiwi: Specialized beaks allow these birds to reach nectar from specific plants!
tooltip.ambientadditions.fun_fact.leaf_f: These amphibians camouflage with leaf litter on the forest floor!
These amphibians camouflage with leaf litter on the forest floor!
tooltip.ambientadditions.fun_fact.longho: These strangely shaped fish are distantly related to the famous pufferfish!
tooltip.ambientadditions.fun_fact.marten: A group of martens is called a 'richness'!
tooltip.ambientadditions.fun_fact.mata_m: These ambush predators mainly dine on fish and other small aquatic creatures!
tooltip.ambientadditions.fun_fact.mole: Declared vermin by some, moles are vital to keeping soil healthy!
tooltip.ambientadditions.fun_fact.mousta: The moustache on these primates is used to identity different members of the species!
tooltip.ambientadditions.fun_fact.naked_: These are the oldest-living type of rodent!
tooltip.ambientadditions.fun_fact.napole: The largest member of the wrasse family, these fish can weigh as much as a gorilla!
tooltip.ambientadditions.fun_fact.nine_b: These armadillos almost always have quadruplet babies!
tooltip.ambientadditions.fun_fact.opah: This is the only known fish that is fully warm-blooded
tooltip.ambientadditions.fun_fact.pancak: While these slugs are generally a pale color, they can have variation in their appearance!
tooltip.ambientadditions.fun_fact.pembro: It's called 'splooting' when a corgi lies down on its stomach with its back legs stretched out!
tooltip.ambientadditions.fun_fact.pink_f: These is the smallest type of armadillo, measuring around the size of a small carrot!
tooltip.ambientadditions.fun_fact.pinocc: The peculiar proboscis on these little lizards is thought to be used in shows of dominance during their mating rituals!
tooltip.ambientadditions.fun_fact.rabbit: These slimy creatures are called rabbit snails due to their lengthy antenna!
tooltip.ambientadditions.fun_fact.red_ri: Red river hog piglets sometimes play dead when startled!
tooltip.ambientadditions.fun_fact.ring_t: These primates have a tail longer than their body!
tooltip.ambientadditions.fun_fact.rubber: These invertebrates have fourteen legs, the same amount as a lobster!
tooltip.ambientadditions.fun_fact.shame_: These crabs are referred to as 'shame faced' due to the way they hold their pincers to cover their face!
tooltip.ambientadditions.fun_fact.siaman: These apes make loud booming calls in the early morning!
tooltip.ambientadditions.fun_fact.sloth_: These bears often dine on termites and ants, and can completely close their nostrils to prevent pests from entering!
tooltip.ambientadditions.fun_fact.spider: These venomous snakes have a unique tail resembling a creepy-crawly which they use to lure in unsuspecting prey!
tooltip.ambientadditions.fun_fact.stag_b: Despite their intimidating mandibles, these beetles have a diet consisting of tree sap and decomposing fruits!
tooltip.ambientadditions.fun_fact.veiled: These lizards are able to move their eyes independently from one another!
tooltip.ambientadditions.fun_fact.white_: These small charismatic bats sport white fur coats, something only seen in a small amount of bat species!
tooltip.ambientadditions.fun_fact.yeti_c: These deep sea-dwelling crabs filter out and eat microorganisms using the fibers on their arms!
